 :tx/rationale "GENESIS-1: DOGFOOD-2 Session 2 ROOT CAUSE CHAIN. Surface: connections scored 3.0/10 (Jaccard keyword similarity). One level down: the connection engine treats observations as bags of words — it has no model of what the observations are ABOUT. Two levels down: braid has NO MODEL OF THE PROJECT AT ALL — it stores text strings, not structural knowledge. Three levels down: the LLM agent already HAD the structural knowledge (it read the code, understood imports, traced dependencies) but when it communicated via braid observe, all structure was discarded by keyword tokenization. Deepest: the interface between LLM (rich associative structure) and braid (persistent store) is a LOSSY FUNNEL. The LLM's activation space encodes ~100K bits of semantic information per observation. The keyword bag retains ~100 bits. This is an information-theoretic bottleneck, not a connection-algorithm bug. The five solutions proposed earlier (multi-signal connections, coverage map, trajectory response, bootstrap surfacing, clustering) are all HEURISTICS TO COMPENSATE FOR NOT PRESERVING THE LLM'S SEMANTIC STRUCTURE. The real fix: preserve the LLM's associative structure at observation intake time."
